<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusi=
ness.com/click/29825673.271828/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9hcnRpY2xlcy9CTC1S=
RUItMjAyMQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB9b5c9423" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemsc=
ope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoratio=
n: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000;=
 border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> lesson of traditiona=
l finance</a> that crypto is learning these days is: =E2=80=9CIf you=E2=80=
=99ve got a bazooka, and people know you=E2=80=99ve got it, you may not hav=
e to take it out.=E2=80=9D For instance:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">There is a small opaque crypto lendin=
g platform that is rumored to be in trouble.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bot=
tom: 5px;">Its depositors want their money back.=C2=A0</li>=09<li style=3D"=
margin-bottom: 5px;">It doesn=E2=80=99t have their money, either because th=
e money is locked up in long-term loans or because it lost the money or <a =
href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29825673.271828/aHR0c=
HM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTEtMTAvZnR4LWlz=
LXN0aWxsLWxvb2tpbmctZm9yLW1vbmV5P2NtcGlkPUJCRDExMjgyMl9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9=
tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIyMTEyOCZ1dG1fY2=
FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB574d70ea" itemprop=3D"Sto=
ryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; =
text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-c=
olor: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  some =
combination</a> or otherwise.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Ther=
e is a =E2=80=9Crun on the bank.=E2=80=9D</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom=
: 5px;">To solve the problem, the lending platform agrees to take a <a href=
=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29825673.271828/aHR0cHM6L=
y93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTEtMDgvYmluYW5jZS1z=
LXpoYW8tc2JmLWVkLWZ0eC1zLWJhbmttYW4tZnJpZWQ_Y21waWQ9QkJEMTEyODIyX01PTkVZU1R=
VRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjIxMT=
I4JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB61b4bda6" itemp=
rop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color:=
 #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; borde=
r-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc=
;">  desperation bailout</a> from some bigger, more stable, better-known cr=
ypto exchange. The big exchange agrees to guarantee the lending platform=E2=
=80=99s customer deposits, or at least gives it an ample line of credit to =
pay out depositors. In exchange, the exchange gets to take over the lending=
 platform, and its existing owners get more or less nothing.</li>=09<li sty=
le=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The run on the bank=C2=A0<em>stops</em>. The dep=
ositors don=E2=80=99t want their money back, because now instead of being d=
epositors at the small lending platform, they are depositors of the large s=
table crypto exchange. Their money is safe, backed by the deep pockets of t=
he large exchange, and they can go back to earning crypto interest or whate=
ver.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you can get a big enough line of credit, yo=
u never need to draw on it, because your depositors were worried about your=
 liquidity, and the line of credit resolves those worries.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In some rough sense this describes the bailout=
s this summer of BlockFi Inc. and Voyager Digital Ltd. by Sam Bankman-Fried=
=E2=80=99s crypto exchange FTX and its affiliated trading firm Alameda Rese=
arch.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-1" style=3D"color: #0000=
00; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bott=
om-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: =
transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a> BlockFi and Voyager looked risky after some of their borrowers collaps=
ed, so customers rushed to withdraw their money, and BlockFi and Voyager di=
dn=E2=80=99t have enough to give them.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And then FTX/Alameda showed up and said, well,=
 we=E2=80=99ll take over your customers. In the case of BlockFi, FTX gave i=
t a line of credit to cash out customers, and got <a href=3D"https://link.m=
ail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29825673.271828/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJ=
nLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDctMDEvZnR4LXVzLXNpZ25zLW9wdGlvbi10by1hY3=
F1aXJlLWJsb2NrZmktZm9yLXVwLXRvLTI0MC1taWxsaW9uP2NtcGlkPUJCRDExMjgyMl9NT05FW=
VNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIy=
MTEyOCZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB6ce59e86" i=
temprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"co=
lor: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; b=
order-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: =
#ccc;">  an option to buy the company</a> for some nominal amount of money.=
 In the case of Voyager, it filed for bankruptcy, and <a href=3D"https://li=
nk.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29825673.271828/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21=
iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTEtMTUvZnR4LXMtMS00LWJpbGxpb24tZGVhbC=
1mb3ItYmFua3J1cHQtY3J5cHRvLWxlbmRlci12b3lhZ2VyLXZvaWQ_Y21waWQ9QkJEMTEyODIyX=
01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rl=
cm09MjIxMTI4JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB2fa22=
ac9" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;">  FTX offered to come in</a>, move Voyager=E2=80=99s customers=
 to FTX, and cash out anyone who wanted out. In either case the basic point=
 was that FTX had enough money to cash out everyone, so=C2=A0<em>no one nee=
ded to cash out</em>. These small rickety crypto firms were rescued by a bi=
g safe crypto firm, so the customers could let their money ride.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Oops! That was all wrong; FTX had been misplac=
ing tons of=C2=A0<em>its=C2=A0</em>customers money, and did=C2=A0<em>not=C2=
=A0</em>in fact have enough to bail out everyone else; FTX <a href=3D"https=
://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29825673.271828/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYm=
xvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTEtMTQvZnR4LXMtYmFsYW5jZS1za=
GVldC13YXMtYmFkP2NtcGlkPUJCRDExMjgyMl9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwm=
dXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIyMTEyOCZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXl=
zdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBff90d512" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  filed for bankruptcy</=
a> earlier this month. <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/c=
lick/29825673.271828/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLz=
IwMjItMTEtMjgvYmxvY2tmaS1sYXRlc3QtdG8tZ28tYmFua3J1cHQtaW4tYWZ0ZXJtYXRoLW9mL=
WZ0eC1zLW1lbHRkb3duP2NtcGlkPUJCRDExMjgyMl9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1h=
aWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIyMTEyOCZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9=
uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBad16dd7b" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" items=
cope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decorati=
on: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000=
; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  And today</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">BlockFi Inc. filed for bankruptcy, the latest =
crypto firm to collapse in the wake of crypto exchange FTX=E2=80=99s rapid =
downfall.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">BlockFi said in a statement that it will use t=
he Chapter 11 process to =E2=80=9Cfocus on recovering all obligations owed =
to BlockFi by its counterparties, including FTX and associated corporate en=
tities,=E2=80=9D adding that recoveries are likely to be delayed by FTX=E2=
=80=99s own bankruptcy. Chapter 11 bankruptcy allows a company to continue =
operating while working out a plan to repay creditors. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Citing =E2=80=9Ca lack of clarity=E2=80=9D ove=
r the status of bankrupt FTX and Alameda Research, the Jersey City, New Jer=
sey-based company earlier halted withdrawals and said it was exploring =E2=
=80=9Call options=E2=80=9D with outside advisers.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">FTX US is listed in the company=E2=80=99s peti=
tion as one of its top unsecured creditors, with a $275 million loan.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The company=E2=80=99s largest unsecured credit=
or, Ankura Trust Company, is owed about $729 million, according to the peti=
tion. Ankura acts as a trustee for BlockFi=E2=80=99s interest-bearing crypt=
o accounts, according to its website.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">BlockFi in July received a capital injection f=
rom a now-collapsed FTX US, and also had collateralized loans to Sam Bankma=
n-Fried=E2=80=99s trading firm Alameda Research.=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It is early yet, and hard to know exactly what=
 happened, but I think it=E2=80=99s something like =E2=80=9Cas long as peop=
le assume you have a bazooka you don=E2=80=99t need to use it, or have it.=
=E2=80=9D When FTX was a $32 billion company that ran a well-regarded crypt=
o exchange, had raised billions of dollars of equity from big investors and=
 was handing out nine-digit credit lines like candy, everyone was like =E2=
=80=9Cah well if FTX is here then everything is fine,=E2=80=9D and it was. =
When FTX was bankrupt and couldn=E2=80=99t fund its credit lines, its benef=
iciaries quickly collapsed along with it.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Here is <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomberg=
business.com/click/29825673.271828/aHR0cHM6Ly9yZXN0cnVjdHVyaW5nLnJhLmtyb2xs=
LmNvbS9ibG9ja2ZpL0hvbWUtRG9ja2V0SW5mbw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBf9af7db1" i=
temprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"co=
