<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusi=
ness.com/click/29825673.271828/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9u=
L2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMTAtMDcvbWF0dC1sZXZpbmUtcy1tb25leS1zdHVmZi1sb29raW5nLWZ=
vci10ZXRoZXItcy1tb25leT9jbXBpZD1CQkQxMTI4MjJfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPW=
VtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMjExMjgmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduP=
W1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBad2e8de8" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" it=
emscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decor=
ation: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000=
000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> basic move in fi=
nance</a> is:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You have some cash flows.</li>=09<li =
style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You put them all into a box.</li>=09<li style=
=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You slice the box into junior and senior claims.</=
li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You sell the senior claims to peopl=
e who want safe cash flows, and the junior claims to people who want exciti=
ng leveraged risk.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Everything is like this: Every company does so=
me business that brings in some cash, and the cash goes first to pay off th=
e company=E2=80=99s debt (its senior claims), and if there=E2=80=99s cash l=
eft over it goes to the company=E2=80=99s shareholders (the junior claimant=
s). Lending money to the company is safer than buying its stock, because yo=
u get paid back first, but buying the stock has more upside.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But you can do this with lots of other cash fl=
ows, and it has come to be known as =E2=80=9Csecuritization.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0=
Most famously, you have a bunch of subprime mortgage bonds, you put them in=
to a collateralized debt obligation, you slice it into junior and senior tr=
anches, you get the most senior tranches rated AAA and sell them to banks s=
eeking safety, you leave the most junior tranches unrated and give them to =
people who want a lot of mortgage risk. This became the template for this s=
ort of thing, so =E2=80=9Ccollateralized ____ obligation=E2=80=9D became th=
e standard term:=C2=A0collateralized debt obligation (CDO) for mortgages, c=
ollateralized loan obligation (CLO) for corporate loans, etc. In 2008, CDOs=
 caused problems, and the market for subprime mortgage CDOs still hasn=E2=
=80=99t recovered. But there are still lots of other cash-flow-slicing busi=
nesses, many of them using the C_O terminology, and you can still occasiona=
lly read articles about how =E2=80=9Cthe same technology that caused the 20=
08 mortgage crisis is coming for=E2=80=9D some other business.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Much of this involves taking medium-safe cash =
flows and parceling them into very safe and pleasingly risky cash flows. A =
subprime mortgage will probably get paid back, but the appetite for probabl=
y-get-paid-back mortgage risk seems to be less than the combined appetite f=
or (1) very very safe senior mortgage risk plus (2) riskier but higher-yiel=
ding mortgage risk. Same with leveraged corporate loans or <a href=3D"https=
://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29825673.271828/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYm=
xvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL25ld3NsZXR0ZXJzLzIwMTktMDgtMjkvbW9uZXktc3R1ZmYtc=
HV0LXlvdXItYnVzaW5lc3MtaW4tYS1ib3g_Y21waWQ9QkJEMTEyODIyX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRt=
X21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjIxMTI4JnV0bV9=
jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB516a85a2" itemprop=3D"St=
oryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000;=
 text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-=
color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">fast-f=
ood franchises</a> or whatever. But you can do it with very risky stuff, if=
 you want. We <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/2982=
5673.271828/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjE=
tMTAtMDcvbWF0dC1sZXZpbmUtcy1tb25leS1zdHVmZi1sb29raW5nLWZvci10ZXRoZXItcy1tb2=
5leT9jbXBpZD1CQkQxMTI4MjJfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY=
2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMjExMjgmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f=
07ceef4b8524a319a23cCad2e8de8" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscop=
e" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !import=
ant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-=
style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> previously talked about</a> this ba=
sic move =E2=80=94=C2=A0put stuff in a box, issue junior and senior claims =
=E2=80=94=C2=A0as a way to create decentralized=C2=A0<em>stablecoins </em>i=
n crypto. You put $2 worth of risky cryptocurrency=C2=A0in a box, you issue=
 a $1 senior claim on the box and call it a =E2=80=9Cstablecoin=E2=80=9D th=
at is always worth a dollar, and you give someone else a $1 levered risky c=
rypto bet. If the $2 worth of cryptocurrency rises to $5, the levered junio=
r claimant does well; if it falls to $1, the levered junior claim is wiped =
out but the stablecoin is still worth $1. If the $2 worth of cryptocurrency=
 falls to $0.0001, <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click=
/29825673.271828/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLz=
IwMjItMDUtMTEvdGVycmEtZmxvcHM_Y21waWQ9QkJEMTEyODIyX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZ=
Gl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjIxMTI4JnV0bV9jYW1w=
YWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBd70797ca" itemprop=3D"StoryLi=
nk" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text=
-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color=
: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> as happens=
</a>, then the stablecoin is no longer stable, oops.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Every few years I read someone <a href=3D"http=
s://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29825673.271828/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuY=
mxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMTgtMTAtMDIvbWVldC13YWxsLXN0cmVl=
dC1zLWxhdGVzdC1mcmFua2Vuc3RlaW4_Y21waWQ9QkJEMTEyODIyX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21=
lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjIxMTI4JnV0bV9jYW=
