Link" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; te=
xt-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-col=
or: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> proposin=
g to do this with stocks</a>. Like, put the S&amp;P 500 Index in a box, iss=
ue senior claims that pay interest and are pretty safe, issue junior claims=
 that are a levered bet on stocks, I don=E2=80=99t know, like a securitized=
 index margin loan. Fine.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway here=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https://link.=
mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29825673.271828/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZnQuY29tL2=
NvbnRlbnQvZTRjNGZkNjEtMzQxZS00ZjViLTlhNDYtNzk2ZmMzYmRjYjAz/607f07ceef4b8524=
a319a23cBf66857f6" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D=
"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-=
bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid=
; background-color: #ccc;">the Financial Times on collateralized fund oblig=
ations</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The product is known as a =E2=80=9Ccollaterali=
sed fund obligation=E2=80=9D and its aim is to diversify risk by parceling =
up the companies providing returns. CFOs are, in some ways, a private equit=
y variant of =E2=80=9Ccollateralised debt obligations=E2=80=9D, the bundles=
 of mortgage-backed securities that only reached the public consciousness w=
hen they wreaked havoc during the 2008 financial crisis.=C2=A0=E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The vehicle exposed to Envision is one of seve=
ral CFOs launched by Azalea, an independently-run unit of the Singapore sta=
te-owned investor Temasek. It is more transparent than most because it is o=
ffered to retail investors, though Azalea does not tell those investors whi=
ch portfolio companies they are exposed to, citing =E2=80=9Cconfidentiality=
 obligations=E2=80=9D.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In effect, the CFO is a box containing stakes =
in 38 private equity and growth funds that Azalea committed money to. The f=
unds are managed by many of the industry=E2=80=99s biggest names including =
Blackstone, KKR, Carlyle and General Atlantic. ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The CFO issues senior and junior bonds, which =
can be bought by retail investors and which offer fixed interest payments o=
f 4.1 per cent and 6 per cent. When the 38 funds hand cash to their investo=
rs, the CFO uses it to make interest payments, then holds some back in a re=
serve account designed to ultimately pay off the principal.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Any remaining cash, after debt repayments and =
expenses, goes to the holders of the CFO=E2=80=99s equity, in this case Aza=
lea itself. Owning the equity is =E2=80=9Cnothing more than a levered inves=
tment into private equity=E2=80=9D, says Jeff Johnston, chairman of the Fun=
d Finance Association.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">S&amp;P Global and Fitch rate the senior bonds=
 in Azalea=E2=80=99s CFO as A+, an investment-grade rating that means it is=
 deemed unlikely to default, and is far higher than the typical junk-grade =
ratings of individual private equity-owned companies.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Azalea told the FT that it structured transact=
ions with =E2=80=9Cdownside risk mitigation in mind=E2=80=9D, using =E2=80=
=9Cconservative=E2=80=9D loan-to-value ratios and putting =E2=80=9Cvarious =
structural safeguards=E2=80=9D in place to protect investors.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Yeah look if your private equity investments r=
eturn 15% per year and you can lever them up by borrowing long-term from re=
tail at 4% per year then that is a pretty good trade?=C2=A0</p>
