<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">How can you obtain Musk proximity? I don=E2=80=
=99t really know =E2=80=94=C2=A0nothing in this column is ever=C2=A0Musk pr=
oximity advice<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-2" style=3D"col=
or: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; bo=
rder-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; backgroun=
d-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[2]</span>
</a>=C2=A0=E2=80=94=C2=A0but, look, in these circumstances, it would be=C2=
=A0<em>understandable=C2=A0</em>if you resorted to techniques of ancient ma=
gic? Like if you were to sculpt a giant metal idol of Musk, you might go ah=
ead and assume that the idol would have some valuable magical effect on you=
r crypto project? And if you were to offer up that idol as an gift to Musk =
himself, and if he were to see it and bless it and accept it and perhaps tw=
eet about it,=C2=A0then that would instill your crypto project with Musk=E2=
=80=99s divine spirit in a way that would probably make the price of your t=
okens go up?=C2=A0Is this all stupid? I don=E2=80=99t know? Yes? And yet? A=
ll I am saying is that humans have been offering precious idols to divine p=
owers for thousands more=C2=A0years than they have been building discounted=
 cash flow models in Excel. Do the idols have a better long-term track reco=
rd than the DCF models? That is beyond my expertise. Anyway here is, I thin=
k you will have to agree, <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.co=
m/click/29825673.271828/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9hcnRpY2xlcy9jcnlwdG8tZW5=
